title: Snoop Dogg, figure skating & Tibor Pleiss: What you may have missed from the Utah-Cal game
text:
Snoop Dogg congratulates Dominique Hatfield; Michigan and Utah share love; Jared Norris play goes viral; interception reaction; Jazz rookie Pleiss attends first football game.
Upcoming Games Utah Football Utah football stats & schedule ASU @ Utah Rice-Eccles Stadium, Salt Lake City Oct. 17, 8:00 p.m. 5 Days 0 Hrs 41 Mins 1 Sec More Coverage Fourth-ranked Utes seeking to exorcise the Sun Devils Utah look ahead/behind Utes are the lone undefeated team in the Pac-12 With all of the hoopla surrounding the appearance of ESPN‚Äôs "College GameDay" in Salt Lake City last weekend, it was somewhat difficult to miss out on the game between Utah and California if one was looking for it.
Still, some fun storylines emerged from the contest that may have been missed even by those watching on television. Here are the top five:

2. Michigan and Utah love each other
The Utes ‚Äô victory over the Michigan Wolverines in the Sept. 3 season opener didn‚Äôt seem like a huge deal at the time. Since then, however, Jim Harbaugh and company have been on a tear, winning five straight games. In that span, they‚Äôve only given up 14 points, and have shut out their last three opponents.
All of this means that the two teams ought to be rooting for one another. The better Michigan does, the stronger Utah‚Äôs win over it will look, while the better the Utes do, the Wolverines‚Äô loss to them won‚Äôt look as bad.

Again, if you were watching, it was hard to miss the fact that Goff and Utah quarterback Travis Wilson combined to throw seven interceptions, including four in the second quarter alone.
